Saran leads in refunding lostmoney to cyberfraud victims,"Patna: Saran district has emerged as a frontrunner in combating cyberfrauds and offering restitution to individuals impacted by cyber fraud, with returning a cumulative sum of Rs 10 lakh to the victims, according to a statement issued by the Economic Offences Unit (EOU) on Friday. Meanwhile, Muzaffarpur district has taken the lead in cracking down on cyber criminals with arrest of 14 persons involved in cybercrimes during the month of April. The data showcasing these achievements was collected through a comprehensive evaluation of all cyber police stations across the state. These findings highlight the importance of proactive measures in addressing the increasing threat of cybercrime and ensuring justice to those affected by fraudulent activities, the EOU press release said. As per the EOU, after review of all cyber police stations, ranking is determined on the basis of action taken by all the districts on various parameters like percentage of FIRs registered against reported complaints, total arrests, percentage of arrests and number of cases in which the money was returned to the cyber victims. The top five districts, which have performed well on various parameters, are Saran, Aurangabad, Muzaffarpur, Sitamarhi and Saharsa, an EOU release said. Cyber police station, Aurangabad, has recovered a total amount of Rs 4,03,680 from the cyber frauds. Similarly, it showed commendable performance in arresting cyber criminals and registering FIRs with securing second position in the list. Sitamarhi cyber police station, which comes on the fourth place, recovered a total amount of Rs 39,830 from the criminals. On the other hand, cyber police station, Saharsa, managed to recover only Rs 50,736 from the cybercriminals in April.","Saran district in Bihar has been recognized for its efforts in combating cyberfrauds and providing restitution to victims, having returned a total of Rs 10 lakh to affected individuals. Muzaffarpur district, on the other hand, has excelled in apprehending cyber criminals, having arrested 14 individuals involved in cybercrimes in April alone. These achievements were highlighted in a statement by the Economic Offences Unit (EOU), which evaluated all cyber police stations in the state to determine rankings based on parameters such as FIR registration, total arrests, and money returned to victims. Aurangabad, Sitamarhi, and Saharsa were also recognized for their efforts in addressing cybercrimes.",Crime and Justice,2024-06-01 00:00:00
