 Nagas are most confused about Christianity, where people are religious but not spiritual. Advising the Theology students, he asked them to communicate Gospel truths with the youths, as they are the most affected in the society, caught in dilemma between religion and spirituality. Further, on behalf of his Minister, T.R. Zeliang, he wished success to the College, and said that through ‘Faith’, as its name itself, the college will grow. The ceremony was also entertained by the College students with special songs, and choreography. Vote of Thanks was given by C. Nihekhu Sema, NCS, Board member, FTC and Closing prayer by Rev. Dr. Chen Rengma, Executive Secretary, Nagamese Baptist Churches Associations (NBCA).","The Foundation Stone Laying Ceremony for Faith Theological College (FTC) in Dimapur was held today, marking a significant milestone since its establishment in 2009. Speeches highlighted the challenges for theologians in today's society. The event featured performances by students, and the ceremony concluded with prayers and a vote of thanks.",Technology and Gadgets,2012-11-25 00:00:00
