Proposal to set up IT centre,"DANAPUR: The Railway has proposed setting up an information technology (IT) centre of the East Central Railway (ECR) at Patna. It has become a must keeping in view sudden increase in the number of computerised reservation offices under ECR. According to an ECR official, the new IT centre is likely to be equipped with all modern facilities which will cater to the needs of five divisions under ECR. This centre, which will incur an expenditure up to Rs 1 crore, will certainly lessen the present load on the main computer centres of Delhi and Kolkata, he said. The computerised reservation offices of the three divisions Danapur, Mughalsarai and Dhanbad are at present linked with Kolkata computer centre while Sonepur and Samastipur are linked with the Delhi centre. Thus, the setting up of a new IT centre is essential to run all the computerised reservation offices of these five divisions smoothly in the larger interest of passengers, an ECR official said. Indian Railways have five such centres in the country located at Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, Kolkata and Secunderabad. The proposed centre at Patna will be the sixth prestigious one of the railways. According to sources, railways have already developed their own 'centre for railway information system' (CRIS) at the country level. Linking all computerised reservation offices of the ECR with the CRIS will prove to be more successful. Like the 'servo' of unreserved ticketing system (UTS), railways intend to make a special 'servo' for the computerised reservation centres also, sources said adding that railways could save a huge amount being given to BSNL now for supplying link to railway computerised reservation offices. The sources said railways have also developed their own 'network' at the global level connecting it to satellite service. It is mainly due to this facility that railway network is spreading in every nook and corner of the country to provide more passengers amenities. The 'UTS' facility at Patna is one of them, sources said adding that the Karbhighaiya end of Patna Junction will be developed as the IT centre of ECR keeping in view the fact that 'UTS' and the 'call centre' facilities have been put up there only. Meanwhile, railways have approved the plan to provide 'UTS' facilities at 28 more stations under ECR. The Danapur division is having this facility at 22 stations. Under the 'UTS' facility, one can purchase tickets three days in advance for any station falling within the jurisdiction of ECR, sources said.","The Indian Railways plans to establish an Information Technology (IT) center for the East Central Railway (ECR) in Patna due to the rising number of computerized reservation offices. Expected to cost up to Rs 1 crore, the center will alleviate the burden on main computer centers in Delhi and Kolkata. Currently, Danapur, Mughalsarai, and Dhanbad divisions are linked with Kolkata, while Sonepur and Samastipur are linked with Delhi. The proposed Patna center will be the sixth in India, aiming to enhance passenger services by linking all ECR reservation offices with the Centre for Railway Information System (CRIS) and implementing a dedicated network. Additionally, the Railways plan to expand Unreserved Ticketing System (UTS) facilities at 28 more stations in the ECR region.",National News,2004-11-01 00:00:00
