 way. Now that he has emerged from custody after 24 days, the ball is firmly in the court of the man who seems to have become bigger than his party in the state.""","Former Karnataka Chief Minister BS Yeddyurappa, out on bail, poses challenges for the BJP's central leadership. Despite facing accusations in a land scam, Yeddyurappa retains support, especially among the Lingayat community. The central leadership's decision to ask him to resign has strained relations, and Yeddyurappa's influence was evident when his supporters boycotted LK Advani's rally. His return raises questions about his role within the party and the impact on the crucial Lingayat vote bank in Karnataka.",Politics,2011-11-12 00:00:00
