­llion and dealing with illegal immigration. He is for a tough law to de­al with the problem and give the­ security services the­ power in critical conditions. In conclusion, the MLA's proposals shine a light on how se­rious the situation is. They draw attention to possible­ national security risks and the pressing ne­ed for fast and determine­d steps to reign in illegal immigration in Manipur.","MLA Lourembam Rameshwar Meetei of Keirao Assembly Constituency in Manipur proposed stringent measures to combat illegal immigration from Myanmar, including a 'shoot at sight' policy. Concerned about illegal immigrants obtaining voter cards through marriage and settling in Manipur, he emphasized the need for effective use of the National Register of Citizens (NRC) and biometric tracking. Meetei urged government intervention to prevent further influx and land grabbing, highlighting security risks and advocating tough laws to address the issue promptly.",Politics,2024-03-02 00:00:00
