The coolest felines of the animation world,"From witty problem solvers, alien robots, lazy house cats to crime fighting super kitties — animated cats have caught our fancy and entertained us through the history of animation, starting from Felix, the black-and-white cat created in the silent era. On World Cat Day, we take a look at some of the most popular fictional cats that are bound to make you feel nostalgic. Tom Tom and Jerry have been childhood companions for almost all of us. And while not many would have rooted for Thomas Jasper, or Tom, he sure managed to get laughs every time his traps to catch Jerry hilariously backfired. Although Jerry always won in their cat-and-mouse games, there have been some episodes in which Tom has actually outwitted Jerry. Garfield Think lasagna and an image of Garfield immediately comes to mind. Many of us can relate to this orange cat, who can’t begin his day without a mug of coffee, hates Mondays, is lazy and loves to eat (he loves lasagna). Garfield is hands-down one of the most popular comic strips ever — it holds the Guinness World Record for being the world’s most widely syndicated comic strip. Cheshire Cat Cheshire is the pink and purple cat with piercing yellow eyes and a wide grin from Alice in Wonderland, who gets his kicks from misleading Alice. He can appear and disappear at will and often engages Alice in perplexing conversations. Doraemon Doraemon is a robotic cat from the future, who travels back in time from the 22nd century to help Nobita Nobi, who is often bullied. Doraemon uses his gadgets from the future to get Nobita out of many tricky situations. The manga series debuted in India in 2005 and has since grown in popularity. Chance ‘T-Bone’ Furlong and Jake ‘Razor’ Clawson With a state-of-the-art fighter jet, Turbokat, and high-end weaponry (all made from discarded military parts and weapons), Chance ‘T-Bone’ Furlong and Jake ‘Razor’ Clawson of SWAT Kats: The Radical Squadron are two vigilante pilots of Megakat City, who fight off villains. Oggy Oggy, the blue cat in Oggy and the Cockroaches, would rather spend his days watching TV and eating. Only if it weren’t for the three mischievous cockroaches (Joey, Dee Dee and Marky), who enjoy making Oggy’s life miserable and do just about everything to annoy him.","On World Cat Day, we celebrate the rich history of animated felines who have entertained us over the years. From Tom of ""Tom and Jerry"" fame, known for his failed attempts to catch Jerry the mouse, to the iconic Garfield, who loves lasagna and hates Mondays, these cats have left a lasting impression. The mischievous Cheshire Cat from ""Alice in Wonderland"" baffles Alice with his disappearing acts and enigmatic conversations, while Doraemon, the robotic cat from the future, aids Nobita Nobi with futuristic gadgets. ""SWAT Kats: The Radical Squadron"" features Chance 'T-Bone' Furlong and Jake 'Razor' Clawson, vigilante pilots who defend Megakat City with their advanced fighter jet. Lastly, Oggy from ""Oggy and the Cockroaches"" faces daily antics from three troublesome cockroaches. These animated cats have become beloved characters, each with their own unique charm and personality.",Opinion and Editorial,2017-08-08 00:00:00
