B-Town gets shimmy with neon,"Printed from B-Town gets shimmy with neon TNN | Jan 1, 2014, 12.00 AM IST B-Town gets shimmy with neon It’s pouring colours in Bollywood songs with bright and catchy neons being the hot favs. And this time it’s not only the leading ladies in bright pinks and yellows lightening up the screen, but Bollywood boys are just as shiny bright. With so many colours on the big screen, it just couldn’t get any better and brighter. Here’s few of those who took the colour palette to the shinier side of the spectrum. Har Kissi Ko | Boss Aditi Rao Hydari Dancing to the remix version of Har Kissi Ko Nahi Milta, Aditi Rao Hydari looks sizzling in a neon green flowy dress that really brightens up the screen. While the rest of the film sees her dressed in simple salwar kurtas, Aditi also flaunts a neon pink bikini and a perfectly carved bikini bod effortlessly and the bright colors only add to the visual appeal. Party On My Mind | Race 2 Deepika Padukone and Jacqueline Fernandez This one’s the most colourful of all the neon songs with two of the hottest ladies of Bollywood, Deepika Padukone and Jacqueline Fernandez, gyrating to the party song. While Deepika sizzles in a neon pink, Jacqueline hits the floor in a neon green dress. And both the leading ladies look hot as ever. Dil Tu Hi Bata | Krrish 3 Hrithik Roshan While it was only the girls who donned the neons earlier, this time, even Bollywood boys are taking on to the colour. And who better than Hrithik himself to flaunt a colour that catches your eyes? Set in the white and blue backdrop of the Dead Sea, Hrithik’s neon yellow shirt, giving enough scope for his fab abs to be visible, brings that additional oomph to the colour palette. Tooh | Gori Tere Pyaar Mein Kareena Kapoor Khan Kareena Kapoor, dressed to sizzle in a blue sharara with a tinge of neon pink, is simply ‘Tooh’ hot to handle. Even though there were stark criticism over the lyrics, Kareena maintained that she had fun while doing the song. And it sure struck a chord with the audience, who only want to let their hair down and dance to the tunes. Saree Ke... | R...Rajkumar Sonakshi Sinha Set against a pristine white background of the Rann of Kutch, it’s a visual delight to watch Sonakshi and Shahid dance to Saree Ke Fall Sa. And Sonakshi’s neon pink stripe on her ghaghra and a neon yellow chunari really stand out in the white and blue background. When such are the visuals, who cares about the lyrics, eh? Tu Bhi Mood... | Grand Masti Mariyam Zakaria Dancing in the rain, dressed in a bright neon green, Mariyam Zakaria makes even a cold rainy evening seem like a scorcher. And it’s the colours that make her stand out with two other equally hot ladies in the song. A perfect eye candy of a song for the guys.","Bollywood's love affair with neon colors lights up the screen in recent films. From Aditi Rao Hydari's sizzling neon green dress in ""Boss"" to Deepika Padukone and Jacqueline Fernandez's vibrant outfits in ""Race 2,"" neon hues dominate dance numbers. Hrithik Roshan joins the trend in ""Krrish 3"" with a striking neon yellow shirt, showcasing his abs against a Dead Sea backdrop. Kareena Kapoor Khan dazzles in a neon-accented sharara in ""Gori Tere Pyaar Mein,"" while Sonakshi Sinha's neon pink and yellow attire in ""R...Rajkumar"" contrasts beautifully with the Rann of Kutch's white landscape. Neon colors add an electrifying visual appeal to Bollywood songs, creating eye-catching moments for viewers.",Entertainment,2014-01-01 00:00:00
