Cleaning stains on suede footwear,"Here are tips on how to clean stains on your pretty suede footwear - Use a suede cleaning brush, tooth brush or cloth to clean out dry stains, dirt and scuff marks on your suede shoes. Always to brush in one direction. Do not brush back and forth. - You can also use a white eraser on stubborn stains. Do not use coloured erasers as they might leave back colour on the suede. After rubbing on the stain, brush the area to maintain the texture of the suede. - Want to get rid of watermarks on suede shoes? Spray the entire shoe with water and rub the watermark with a cloth. Stuff it with newspaper to maintain the shape of the shoe and let it air dry for a few days. Using a dryer to hasten the process will leave stain the shoe even more. - Rub the shoe with a cloth dipped in a mixture of vinegar and water. This cleans stains fabulously. Although the shoes might smell for a few days, letting them air dry should solve the problem.","To clean suede shoes, brush away dirt and stains using a suede cleaning brush, toothbrush, or cloth. Always brush in one direction to avoid damaging the suede. For stubborn stains, apply a white eraser and brush the area to maintain the texture. To remove watermarks, spray the shoe with water, rub the stain, and stuff it with newspaper to dry. To remove general stains, use a cloth dampened with a vinegar-water mixture. Allow the shoes to air dry to prevent further staining.",Lifestyle and Features,2013-04-19 00:00:00
