Tiger all but extinct in Telangana SECTIONS Tiger all but extinct in Telangana,"he national animal, tiger, has all but disappeared from the newest state in the country. The situation is so alarming that wildlife officials say there is a very real danger of the tiger going locally extinct in Telangana in the next two or three years. In the latest census conducted this summer, no evidence of tigers was found in Eturnagaram, Pakhal wildlife reserves in Warangal, Pranahita and Jannaram reserves in Adilabad and Kinnerasani reserve in Khammam districts. According to sources in the state wildlife department, the presence of tigers was recorded only in Kawal in Adilabad, which was declared a tiger reserve in 2012, and in the thin strip of the Papikonda national park in Khammam which falls in Telangana. The remaining portion of the reserve, along with seven mandals of Khammam, was made a part of Andhra Pradesh post bifurcation.","The Uttarakhand state police are intensifying search operations for BJP legislator Rajkumar Thukral, who has been evading arrest for over three months. Thukral is wanted in connection with riots that occurred in Rudrapur in 2011, where four people were killed and 60 injured. The police have attached several of Thukral's properties and have begun the process of chargesheeting him. Thukral was declared an absconder by a local court in November. ...",Miscellaneous,2014-05-10 00:00:00
