e Telangana an appeal- ing prospect for diverse investment portfolios. The recent WEF summit in Davos proved to be a sig- nificant milestone for Telangana, with FDI deals nearly doubling as the state attracted investments worth over Rs 40,000 crore, the highest-ever, in the Davos summit held in January this year. This achievement came just weeks after the new gov- ernment took office on December 7, 2023, indicat- ing the effectiveness of its swift action and clear poli-","Telangana has recorded a significant achievement in Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) with inflows amounting to $3 billion in the fiscal year 2024, marking a doubling of investments compared to the previous year. This surge positions Telangana as the second-highest recipient of FDI in India, trailing only Gujarat. Industry analysts credit this success to the business-friendly initiatives and policy-driven approach adopted by the Congress-led government under Chief Minister A. Revanth Reddy. His proactive promotion of Telangana as a prime investment destination, notably highlighted during the World Economic Forum (WEF) summit in Davos earlier in the year, has been instrumental in attracting global investors. The state's strategic positioning and focused efforts to improve infrastructure, ease of doing business, and sector-specific incentives have bolstered investor confidence. Telangana's burgeoning sectors such as information technology, pharmaceuticals, and manufacturing have particularly benefited from this influx of foreign capital. While Gujarat leads in total FDI inflows, Telangana's impressive growth rate underscores its emergence as a competitive economic hub in India. The momentum generated by these investments is expected to further propel the state's economic growth and development initiatives in the coming years.",Local News,2024-06-24 00:00:00
