e information to the media to tarnish his image. He also termed the actions of the PF authorities arbitrary, high-handed, and illegal","The Karnataka High Court stayed proceedings and an arrest warrant against cricketer Robin Uthappa, who was a former director of Centuries Lifestyle Brand Private Limited. The company failed to deposit employee PF contributions, leading to actions by the Regional PF Commissioner. Uthappa, who resigned in May 2020 after the company breached financial commitments, argued that he was not responsible for day-to-day management or as an employer. He had clarified these facts with PF authorities, claiming the arrest warrant was unjustified and aimed at tarnishing his image. Uthappa termed the PF authorities' actions arbitrary and illegal.",Crime and Justice,2024-12-31 00:00:00
