"March quarter will be robust for us: Yogen Lal, COO, Unity Infra","Whatis the revenue conversion timeline of current projects on hand and how many projects are you L1 bidder in? Current visibility from our order book is for around 28 to 30 months. In terms of value, we would have an L1 position in approximately 360 to 400 crores of projects. ould you walk us through how many projects are you running cost or time overruns on? Most of our projects are running on time. Only because of this rigorous monsoon that we had recently - in the north and the west, particularly - it was accentuated. There might be a slight time overrun but that will be made up in this working season. What kind of penalties do you have ifthese projects are not finished? Are there heavy penalties for not completing on time and ifthatis the case and how do these guys get away by leaving highways on for 10-10, 20-20 years? There are liquidated damages to the tune of 5% of the contract value generally across contracts. But those are for reasons which are attributable to the contractor or the construction entity which is undertaking that project. Since you have spoken about the road project in general, there are so many instances of land acquisition deals. For instance, we are doing a project in Mumbai, JVLR where the last 1 kilometre is still encroached and that has not been removed for the last probably 4 or 5 years. So in such cases, the contractor has very little to do because this is, after all, the responsibility of the government. In the next 1 or 2 quarters, which of your significant projects are nearing completion or you expect a bigger payment coming through because that projectis either getting completed or perhaps it may be in the next year March quarter or June quarter? Traditionally, the fourth quarter of the fiscal is the strongest for any construction company because this is the commencement of the working season. We expect that around 5-6 projects will be completed in the next 5-6 months. So we do expect that the March quarter will be quite robust for the company as it has historically been.","The company anticipates a revenue conversion timeline of 28 to 30 months, with an L1 position in projects worth 360 to 400 crores. Most projects run on schedule, with minor delays due to recent monsoons. Penalties for delays typically amount to 5% of the contract value. Expectations are high for a robust March quarter, with 5-6 projects nearing completion.",Construction/Infrastructure,2010-10-14 00:00:00
