"New I-T Bill, mines law on monsoon session agenda","The monsoon session of Parliament, scheduled to be held between July 21 and August 21, will take up a few economic Bills, including the Income Tax Bill, 2025 that seeks to simplify the provisions of the direct tax laws. However, two widely watched pieces of legislation namely the Insurance (Amendment) Bill and Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) Bill are conspicuously absent from the Bills listed for the session. The insurance Bill seeks to allow 100% foreign direct investment (FDI) and composite licensing, while the amendments to the IBC 2016 are designed to expedite the pace of resolution of stressed assets, and bring in a few new provisions like those for cross-border and group insolvency resolutions.","The Monsoon Session of Parliament, from July 21 to August 21, will consider several economic bills, including the Income Tax Bill, 2025, aimed at simplifying direct tax laws. However, the anticipated Insurance (Amendment) Bill and Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) Bill are not on the agenda. These omitted bills involve key reforms—100% FDI in insurance and faster, broader insolvency resolutions, respectively.",Politics,2025-07-16 00:00:00
EFTA deal with India could be signed before 2024 elections: Swiss envoy,"Switzerland's Ambassador to India, Ralf Heckner, has expressed optimism that the crucial European Free Trade Association (EFTA) deal with the country would be wrapped up before the 2024 general elections. Heckner stressed on the importance of the proposed trade deal for unlocking innovation and investment opportunities. ""Both sides have been negotiating very closely and seriously over the last more than 12 months. I remain positive that the deal would be wrapped up before the (2024) elections,"" he told PTI. The envoy was recently in the city to unveil the Kolkata chapter of the Swiss-India Chamber of Commerce. Parliamentary elections in India are due in early 2024. ""If India wants innovation, it needs to work with about 12 to 15 countries, and one of those countries is Switzerland for a world of investments and innovation,"" We will have a more strategic innovation relationship with India, Heckner stated. India and the EFTA states Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway, and Switzerland - are negotiating a Trade and Economic Partnership Agreement (TEPA) with a view to boost economic ties between the two regions. Negotiations on the agreement were officially launched in January 2008. The EFTA members are not part of the European Union (EU). Noting the sharp rise in visa application processing numbers, which hit a record 2 lakh in 2023 compared to pre-COVID levels of 1.6-1.7 lakh, Heckner said this trend would lead to enhanced trade and cultural ties between India and Switzerland in the years ahead. The EFTA-India merchandise trade exceeded USD 6.1 billion in 2022.","Switzerland's Ambassador to India, Ralf Heckner, expressed optimism about finalizing the European Free Trade Association (EFTA) deal with India before the 2024 general elections. The proposed trade deal between India and the EFTA states (Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway, and Switzerland) aims to enhance economic ties. Heckner emphasized the importance of the trade deal for unlocking innovation and investment opportunities, highlighting that working with countries like Switzerland is crucial for India's innovation aspirations. The EFTA-India merchandise trade exceeded $6.1 billion in 2022. The ambassador noted a significant increase in visa applications, reaching a record 200,000 in 2023, which is expected to contribute to enhanced trade and cultural ties between India and Switzerland in the coming years. Negotiations on the Trade and Economic Partnership Agreement (TEPA) between EFTA and India were officially launched in January 2008.",Business and Finance,2023-12-10 00:00:00
Celebs who have frozen their eggs for delayed motherhood,"With Khloe Kardashian and Lamar Odomhav ing called off their on-going divorce proceedings and having reunited, post his near death experience, she has been advised by sister Kim to follow her example and have her eggs frozen. Khole reportedly has laughed off the suggestion of becoming the Kardashian clan's second member to do so, as she feels she is not old enough to be concerned about it, just yet.While the Kardashian sisters figure it out, we tell you of other Hollywood celebs who have taken the help of science to freeze their progeny for a delayed yet almost certain tryst with maternity .KIM KARDASHIAN In the 2012 series of the show, Keeping Up with the Kardashians, Kim, who was 31 then, underwent oocyte cryopreservation. At a trip to a fertility specialist with sister Khloe, who too was struggling with pregnancy issues while married to Lamar, Kim took the call to freeze her eggs. She said, in her show, I'm glad that I'm freezing my eggs. I think now I can just be proactive, but I want to make sure when the time is right, I want to be prepared. I should be safe. Kim and Kanye are currently parents to North and the pair is pregnant with a baby boy, due in December.SOFIA VERGARA The Columbian bombshell, who is all set to tie the knot with Joe Manganiello, was in the midst of a huge legal battle regarding her frozen eggs. In April this year, the actress' ex, Nick Loeb, filed a lawsuit in California against Vergara's right to detain him from bringing the embryos to life with the help of a surrogate. During their relationship that ended in 2014, the two had cryopreserved female embryos created through IVF and have since been at loggerheads regarding bringing the embryos to life. CELINE DION Singer Celine Dion didn't just freeze her eggs but also used them eight years later to give birth to her twin sons Nelson and Eddy. Celine decided to have her embryos frozen in 2000 while she was using IVF to conceive her first child, Ren-Charles. In 2007, she returned for the embryos that for the past eight years had been kept frozen, to facilitate her second pregnancy.Married to Ren Anglil, hers is one of the landmark celebrity success stories of such medical procedures.For more interesting Hollywood news and pictures follow us on Pinterest>>> timesofindiaFor latest Hollywood updates follow us on G+ >>> The Times of India Entertainment JANET JACKSON In 2008, the then 41-year-old Janet Jackson spoke of how she was considering freezing her eggs till the time she was ready for motherhood.Speaking about it, she said,You can have your eggs frozen. There are all sorts of things you can do these days. In the same interview she also said that while she is `allergic to marriage' she is going to `definitely have kids someday.' So far she has neither confirmed nor negated having had her eggs frozen.MARIA MENOUNOS Actress, journalist, host and occasional professional wrestler, Menounos decided in 2011 at the age of 33, to freeze her eggs. She went public with her decision and said in Good Morning America,It's a bit of an insurance policy. It doesn't mean that in two years or three years I'm not going to try naturally, but at least I have this in case there's a problem. JOANNA KRUPA The Real Housewives of Miami star, Joanna Krupa, revealed in 2014 that having witnessed a friend's struggle getting pregnant, she has decided to freeze her eggs. Calling it a security blanket, the then-35-year-old said that it was her way of ensuring that she did not have to regret a couple of years down the line, when she finally wanted to have kids. BRIDGET MARQUARDT Ex-playmate to Hugh Hefner and Girls Next Door star, Marquardt froze her eggs at 34 when she was living at the Playboy Mansion with Hefner.Going public with her decision three years later, Marquardt said in an interview, Looking back I was like, `It was easy,' but it wasn't that easy.It's a lot of medication, a lot of hormones. You have to inject yourself in the stomach and I'm so terrified of needles! It was a difficult thing for me to do. I wanted to have a little bit of insurance policy and a little extra time. ZSA ZSA GABOR Eminent actress and socialite Zsa Zsa, who tied the knot nine times, also supposedly had her eggs frozen.While Gabor, known to be a woman with an air of mystery around her, never confirmed the news, her 9th husband, Prince Frederic von Anhalt, spoke of how the actress got some of her eggs frozen in the 1960s that somehow got misplaced.CAROLYN MOOS Professional basketball player Carolyn Moos, who was engaged to NBA player Jason Collins, announced her decision to freeze her eggs in 2013. The announcement came in the wake of the news of Collins, whom she had dated for eight years, revealing that he is gay. The then 34-yearold Moos who wanted to have kids, but was unsure how long it would take to meet Mr Right, said, So many women think about this as a plan or option ... but few have had 8 years taken away from them like I did.For latest Hollywood updates follow us on Twitter >>>@TOIEntertainFor the latest in Hollywood news, like us on Facebook >>>TOIEntertainWATCH: Celine Dion - My Heart Will Go On","In 2007, she returned for the embryos that for the past eight years had been kept frozen, to facilitate her second pregnancy.Married to Ren Anglil, hers is one of the landmark celebrity success stories of such medical procedures.For more interesting Hollywood news and pictures follow us on Pinterest>>> timesofindiaFor latest Hollywood updates follow us on G+ >>> The Times of India Entertainment JANET JACKSON In 2008, the then 41-year-old Janet Jackson spoke of how she was considering freezing her eggs till the time she was ready for motherhood.Speaking about it, she said,You can have your eggs frozen.",Entertainment,2015-11-07 00:00:00
