 influence, but we remained firm on following the new formula. If a leader is not accepted in his own ward, how come he becomes the leader of the city,” he asked.Lauding the party’s page committee members, who have the responsibility to ensure that voters reach polling booths during elections, Paatil said: “Prior to the 2022 Assembly elections, I have announced that BJP will win all 182 seats, but we won 156…. The credit of this achievement goes to page committee workers… Big shot leaders of Congress lost seats… some of them, who were initially winning, lost…”In a dig at BJP MLA from Udhna, Manu Patel, who was present at the event, Paatil said: “Manubhai had earlier lost the municipal election and now he won (state polls) by 70,000 votes. The victory is not of the leader, the credit goes to page committee members. I want to advise Patel to be aggressive with officials and not with party workers. We will not tolerate such insults…” “However, since last one year, I have not come across a single complaint against Patel,” he added.","State BJP president C R Paatil has urged party leaders and workers in Surat to spend one hour every Sunday cleaning their surroundings and upload photographs of the same on NaMo and Saral apps. This initiative is aimed at helping Surat reach the first position in the Swachha Bharat Survekshan, as it currently holds the second position. Paatil emphasized the importance of regular efforts to enhance cleanliness in the city, and he urged elected councilors to actively participate in the initiative. He believes that by collectively working towards cleanliness, Surat can secure the top spot among the cleanest cities in India.",Politics,2023-11-25 00:00:00
