India launches a ‘Climate Equity Monitor’ on first day of COP26,"On the first day of the climate change conference, COP26, India launched an online dashboard – the ‘Climate Equity Monitor’ for assessing, at the international level, equity in climate action, inequalities in emissions, energy and resource consumption across the world, and ongoing climate policies of several countries from the perspective of developing countries. The ‘Climate Equity Monitor’ is aimed at monitoring the performance of Annex-I Parties under the UNFCCC (comprising developed countries) based on the foundational principles of the Climate Convention, namely equity and the principle of Common but Differentiated Responsibilities and Respective Capabilities (CBDR-RC). The performance and policies of the Non Annex-I Parties (developing countries) will be also provided for comparison, a release from the Environment, Forests and Climate Change Ministry said. The performance here is the respective countries actions to cut down on carbon emissions as part of the climate actions that will collectively help restrict global temperature rise. Welcoming the going live of the website (https://climateequitymonitor.in) on global climate policy, India’s Environment, Forest and Climate Change Minister, Bhupender Yadav, tweeted: “Climate Equity Monitor that focuses on equity and climate action from a data and evidence-based perspective will encourage a vigorous discussion on this crucial issue and engage experts from all countries.” He also congratulated the team that worked on this project, the release said. The website has been conceptualised and developed by independent researchers from India — the Climate Change Group at the M.S. Swaminathan Research Foundation (MSSRF), Chennai, and the Natural Sciences and Engineering Department at the National Institute of Advanced Studies (NIAS) Bengaluru, with other independent researchers. The MSSRF team was led by Senior Fellow, Climate Change, Professor T. Jayaraman, and the NIAS team by Associate Professor, Dr Tejal Kanitkar. In keeping with the latest scientific results of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) that have underlined the importance of cumulative emissions and carbon budgets, the analysis will be anchored in these two concepts. The equitable sharing of the global carbon budget is the fundamental equity principle that will underpin the assessments that will progressively appear on the website. Existing “tracking” websites on climate policies are based in the global North and routinely do not address the crucial aspects of equity and differentiation. Other websites, according to the researchers, bury the key issues in complexities that are not transparently dealt with. “The developers of this dashboard have taken this initiative to build awareness, especially among the public of the global South, that climate action is a global collective action problem. The website is intended to debunk the narrative provided by many developed countries, and global non-government organizations that focus attention continually on what developing countries must do, constantly demanding greater commitment and action from them,” the release added. The website is expected to be a valuable tool for policy makers, public institutions, researchers, academics, students, and the general public from developing countries to keep equity and climate justice considerations clearly in view in their perspective. The website will also undergo constant upgradation with additional new material, including the addition of new areas such as climate finance, technology transfer and adaptation.","India launched the 'Climate Equity Monitor' on the first day of COP26, aimed at assessing international equity in climate action. Developed by researchers from MSSRF Chennai and NIAS Bengaluru, the dashboard evaluates the performance of Annex-I (developed) and Non Annex-I (developing) countries under the UNFCCC principles. It focuses on emissions, energy consumption, and climate policies, emphasizing equity and the principle of Common but Differentiated Responsibilities. Environment Minister Bhupender Yadav praised the initiative, highlighting its role in promoting global climate discourse and transparency. The website will serve as a resource for policymakers, researchers, and the public, fostering awareness of climate justice and collective global action. Future updates will expand coverage to include climate finance, technology transfer, and adaptation.",Environment,2021-10-31 00:00:00
Heavy rains trigger landslides on Jammu-Srinagar National Highway in Ramban,"Thousands of pilgrims stranded as inclement weather forces suspension of Amarnath Yatra for second day. The annual Amarnath pilgrimage was suspended from Jammu City on Saturday morning following heavy rains that triggered landslides, mudslides and washed away a stretch of road on Jammu-Srinagar National Highway in Ramban district. No fresh batch was allowed on Saturday for the holy cave due to heavy rain and prevailing weather conditions in Kashmir and on Jammu-Srinagar National Highway,” he added. Mountains close to Amarnath shrine also observed light snowfall after heavy showers. “It was heavily raining for hours at Sonmarg and Baltal. So, resumption of yatra wasn’t possible,” said an official posted at Baltal. J&K Lt Governor Manoj Sinha, however, told media persons in Srinagar, if weather improves, yatra could resume from Sunday. Several nullahs and waterbodies are flowing close to the alert mark, with prediction of more rains, control rooms have been set up in south and north Kashmir and people have been asked to contact helpline in case of any emergency","Inclement weather, including heavy rains and landslides, led to the suspension of the annual Amarnath Yatra pilgrimage for the second day. The pilgrimage, starting from Jammu City, was halted due to adverse weather conditions and road damage caused by rains in the Ramban district along the Jammu-Srinagar National Highway. No new batches were permitted on Saturday for the holy cave due to the challenging weather conditions. The mountains near the Amarnath shrine experienced light snowfall after intense showers. Authorities, including J&K Lt Governor Manoj Sinha, are monitoring the situation, with the possibility of resuming the yatra contingent on improved weather conditions. Control rooms have been established, and helplines activated for emergencies due to rising water levels in rivers and water bodies",Weather,2023-07-08 00:00:00
Banking stocks end in red as hopes of further rate cuts by RBI fade,"Bank stocks tanked on Monday as hopes faded away of a rate-cut by the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) in its mid-quarter review of monetary policy 2012-13. The RBI kept key lending rates unchanged to control high inflation. The re-purchase rate remains unchanged at eight percent, which automatically keeps the reverse re-purchase rate at seven percent. The move assumes significance as the RBI was expected to cut these key rates that would have translated in lowering of interest being paid by consumers on their loans for consumer durables, homes or automobiles. Economic experts feel that the bearish consumer sentiment on account of high interest rates will continue. The news dragged the banking stocks down with the bank index at the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) falling 411.20 points around 2:30 pm and stood at 11,175.45 points. Scrips of banking majors such as State Bank of India (SBI), ICICI Bank and HDFC Bank all tumbled. The stock of SBI, India's largest lender, was down 94.80 points or 4.34% and stood at Rs2,112.30, followed by ICICI Bank whose scrip fell by 33.40 points or 3.95% at Rs811.50, and HDFC Bank stock was down 16.50 points or 3.01% at Rs531.35. Realty sector too took a hit with the sectoral index at BSE down 50.95 points at 1,571.91 points. Automobile index too fell by a huge 102.59 points and stood at 9,111.21 points. Scrip of automobile major Maruti Suzuki fell by 23 points or 2.08% at Rs1,085, followed by Tata Motors, down 4.80 points or two percent at Rs235.25, Hero MotoCorp, down 21.05 points or 1.05% at Rs1,979, and Mahindra and Mahindra whose scrip fell by 5.30 points or 0.76 points at Rs692.10 As hopes of a rate-cut by the RBI in its mid-quarter review of monetary policy 2012-13 faded, the 30-scrip sensitive index (Sensex) of the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) slipped 302.31 points around 2:30 pm. The Sensex, which opened at 17,039.54 points, was down 302.31 points, or 1.78 percent from its previous close of 16,949.83 points, and stood at 16,647.52 points. The Sensex touched a high of 17,109.95 points and a low of 16,636.09 points in the early session of trade. The BSE midcap index was down 76.46 points while the smallcap index fell 50.60 points. The wider 50-scrip S&P CNX Nifty of the National Stock Exchange was 1.75% or 89.80 points lower at 5,049.25 points.","Banking stocks ended in the red on Friday as hopes of further rate cuts by the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) faded. The BSE Bankex index fell 0.4% to 31,282.30, while the Nifty Bank index lost 0.3% to 32,630.95. The slide in banking stocks came after the RBI said in its monetary policy statement that it was not comfortable with the current level of inflation and that it would continue to monitor the situation closely. Investors had been hoping for a rate cut by the RBI in order to boost economic growth, but the central bank's hawkish stance sent banking stocks lower.",National News,2013-05-03 00:00:00
Rahul calls PM Modi a ‘specimen’ in US,"RAHUL Gandhi took a dig at Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Wednesday, describing him as a “specimen” who thinks he knows more than God and alleged that the idea of India is under attack, prompting a furious BJP to slam him as a “fake Gandhi” who “insults” India on the foreign soil in his bid to target Modi. BJP leaders launched an all-out attack on the former Congress President for his swipe at Modi and his dispensation, with Information and Broadcasting Minister Anurag Thakur claiming that Gandhi goes abroad on “sponsored programmes” for “anti-India propaganda” to insult the country on the foreign soil. Addressing Indian Americans in Santa Clara in the US, the Congress leader said, “That is the disease. We have a group of people in India, who are absolutely convinced that they know everything. In fact, they think they know even better than God. They can sit down with God and have a conversation and explain to him about what is going on. Of course, our Prime Minister is one such specimen.” Speaking at the ‘Mohabbat Ki Dukaan’ event organised by the Indian Overseas Congress USA, Gandhi also took an apparent jibe at the Modi Government saying these people are “absolutely convinced” that they know everything and can explain history to historians, science to scientists and warfare to the army. “There is a group of people in India who are absolutely convinced they know everything. They think they know even more than God. “They can sit with God and explain to him what’s going on. And of course, our Prime Minister is one such specimen. If you sat Modiji with God, he will explain to God how the universe works and God will get confused about what have I created,” he said, evoking laughter from the audience. Khalistani supporters heckle Rahul Gandhi: CONGRESS leader Rahul Gandhi was heckled by a group of Khalistani supporters who raised slogans against him and briefly interrupted his speech during an event here in the US state of California. An unperturbed Gandhi smiled in response to sloganeering and said: ‘Welcome, welcome ... Nafrat ke bazaar mein mohabbat ki dukan’.","During an event in the US, Rahul Gandhi took a jab at Prime Minister Narendra Modi, describing him as someone who thinks he knows more than God. This sparked backlash from BJP leaders, with Anurag Thakur accusing Gandhi of engaging in anti-India propaganda on foreign soil. Gandhi's remarks highlighted a perceived arrogance in certain Indian leaders. Additionally, Gandhi faced disruption from Khalistani supporters during his speech, prompting him to respond with a message of love amidst hate.",Politics,2023-06-01 00:00:00
Priyanka barefoot walk wows Rae Bareli,"It’s not everyday that they see a celebrity, if not a political leader, walking barefoot. But as Priyanka Gandhi covered about half-a-kilometre barefoot Monday in the scorching heat after her sandals broke during a padyatra in Rae Bareli, she left the onlookers mesmerised. The Congress workers sought to cash-in on the moment as they raised the slogan “Priyanka nahi aandhi hai, doosri Indira Gandhi hai” (She is a storm, and an another Indira Gandhi). Concentrating mainly on Muslim dominated areas and paying visit to the houses of known Muslim faces of Rae Bareli city on the last day of campaigning, Priyanka began her foot-march around 2:20 pm from central office of the party in the city. Advertisement As she took strides, akin to her grandmother and former prime minister Indira Gandhi, she gave a hard time to security officials, who had to push back the teeming crowd around her. After she had covered about one-and-a-half kilometres at Gulab road, someone accidentally stepped on her sandals and the strap came undone. As there were women waiting for her ahead, she took off her other sandal as well and walked bare-foot. As she kept moving, local youth Congress leaders went in search of new pair of sandals in the market. By the time one Rahul Bajpai found a new pair, she had walked another 500 mtrs bare-foot till Qila bazaar area. On her way, some leaders even tried to give her their footwear but she continued walking. She finally accepted an alternative pair of sandals from her aide Priti Sahay. As she stopped at shops, houses, crossings and especially at places where groups of women were standing, security personnel struggled to clear way for her. Ending her campaign at Congress district office, Priyanka told reports that there is no challenge before Congress in Rae Bareli and Amethi. Priyanka will be holding public meetings and padyatra in Amethi, Rahul Gandhi’s constituency, on Tuesday .","Priyanka nahi aandhi hai, doosri Indira Gandhi hai, is a storm. she will be holding public meetings and padyatra in amethi on thursday.",Politics,2014-04-29 00:00:00
"‘Cartels gone’, Hry auctions 60% liquor vending zones","Chandigarh: Having put 60% of liquor vends across Haryana under the hammer in the first round of e-auction for the next excise year, the excise and taxation department claims to have broken the cartel of major players of the state. According to information, in the first round of auction, which was held between May 26 to May 31, the department claims to have sold 731 out of 1,197 liquor zones and has assured the excise licence fee of Rs 5,181 crore against them so far. Officials feel that as 40% of stocks are yet to come under bid for the second time, the department is expecting to achieve its targeted revenue of Rs 13,000 crore in terms of revenue from excise. Alleging some drastic changes added with the increase of excise duty, the major players of the liquor industry in the state had threatened to stay away from vends. Officials claim that during the first round of auction they have been able to break the cartel. “Last time, the department had to conduct 18 rounds of actions to completely sell out all the zones. But this time, we are expecting to exhaust all zones by the next two rounds. We are hopeful of not only improving the transparency and revenue, but we shall maintain more checks on the flow of liquor into vends,’’ a senior official of the department said. According to information, during the auction held last year, the department had been able to sell off 731 vends for Rs 4,282 crore against Rs 5,181 crore of bid money for the current year. According to information, liquor zones of NCR had been a hotcake for the department during the auction which was divided in three groups ie A, B and C. In group A, the department had been able to bring 225 vending zones in a successful allotment out of the total 420 zones. Similarly, in group B, of the total 326 vending zones, 217 had come under bid while the rest were covered under group C. In Gurgaon west zone, the department had been able to sell 79 out of 83 vending zones in group A and 63 out of 79 vending zones of group B for Gurgaon East in the e-auction held on May 31. Similarly, in group C 89 vends out of 111 were sold on the single day in Faridabad. Now there are just 22 vends left. So is the case of other NCR districts like Mewat, Palwal, Rohtak, Sonipat and Panipat.","The Haryana excise and taxation department has claimed success in breaking the cartel of major players in the state's liquor industry by putting 60% of liquor vends under the hammer in an e-auction for the next excise year. The first round of auction, held between May 26 to May 31, saw 731 out of 1,197 liquor zones being sold, assuring an excise licence fee of Rs 5,181 crore so far. With 40% of stocks yet to be auctioned, the department aims to achieve its targeted revenue of Rs 13,000 crore. Last year, the department conducted 18 rounds of auctions to sell all zones, but this year, they expect to complete the process in the next two rounds. The NCR liquor zones were particularly sought-after during the auction.",Business and Finance,2024-06-03 00:00:00
"2 men barge into Mumbai pub with revolver, threaten visitors","MUMBAI: The unit 9 of the city crime branch arrested two persons for allegedly barging into a pub in Amboli in Andheri wielding an illegal weapon and threatening its patrons and misbehaving with women on Monday morning. The pub has been sealed, police said. One of the arrested accused has been identified as Samad Raees Khan (23), a cable operator by profession who has six criminal cases registered against him at Malvani, Oshiwara and Andheri police stations. Police have recovered one revolver from him. The other accused is 56-year-old Mohammed Asif Khan, a dry fruit seller from Millat Nagar in Andheri. Police said both the accused have been booked under the IPC sections 341 (wrongful restrain of a person), 354 A (sexual harassment) and 509 ( word, gesture or act intended to insult the modesty of a woman) and under the Arms Act. The arrests were made by a police team led by inspector Daya Nayak after identifying the two men based on the CCTV footage obtained from the Barrel pub. “Police team analysed the CCTV footage and used its sources to trace the accused from Malwani area. The revolver used in the crime was not licensed. We were also able to trace the victim who was molested,” a police officer said.","Two men, Samad Raees Khan and Mohammed Asif Khan, were arrested by Mumbai's crime branch for threatening patrons and misbehaving with women at a pub in Andheri. Khan, with six criminal cases, was found with an illegal revolver. Both were booked under relevant IPC sections and the Arms Act.",Crime and Justice,2024-01-10 00:00:00
